I'm not sure if this is what you want, but Digital's (DEC) most recent password
hashing alorithm is Purdy-S (they also call it the Hickory algorithm).  But it
is a hashing function; not for encryption/decryption.

If you are still interested, you can get C source that I have succefully run on
the Sun SPARC, Silicon Graphics Crimson Elan, VAX, and Alpha platforms.


anonymous ftp to:

ftp.spc.edu	[.macro32.savesets]hpwd.zip

		or

robot.nuceng.ufl.edu	[.crypto.hpwd]hpwd.zip, vms share files, and raw source


Good luck!
~Shawn

